---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<Base title="Get Started" description="Set up Baxter in minutes — drop the harness into any project, open it in Claude Code, Cursor, or GitHub Copilot, and paste your first raw request.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Get started with Baxter</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
      Baxter is a plain-text harness — a folder you drop into any project. No accounts, no subscriptions, no special tooling. You need git, an AI coding tool (Claude Code, Cursor, or similar), and your project's source code.
    </p>

    <!-- What you'll have at the end -->
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-primary-200 bg-primary-50 p-5 dark:border-primary-800/40 dark:bg-primary-900/10">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-300">What you'll have at the end of this guide</p>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>Baxter installed and reading your codebase</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>Your first artefact generated and saved to git</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>A clear understanding of how to invoke each artefact type</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- coderepo callout — must be unmissable -->
    <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl border-2 border-primary-500 bg-primary-50 p-6 dark:border-primary-700 dark:bg-primary-950/30">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">Most important step — where does my code go?</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">→ <code class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">coderepo/</code></p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Copy or symlink your project's source code into the <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> folder. Baxter reads it to run multi-dimensional sanity checking on every artefact — feasibility, logic, data model, roles, naming, edge cases, and UX challenges. Without this, artefact verification cannot run.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-primary-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-primary-800">
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">agentic-ba/
├── <span class="text-primary-400 font-bold">coderepo/</span>        ← YOUR PROJECT SOURCE CODE HERE
│   └── (your app, API, schema, migrations…)
├── artefacts/
│   ├── bugs/        ← bug reports
│   ├── changes/     ← change requests
│   ├── ai-features/ ← AI feature specs
│   ├── requirements/← business requirements documents
│   ├── product-docs/← product documentation
│   ├── implementation/ ← technical implementation plans
│   ├── test-suites/ ← test cases
│   ├── diagrams/    ← diagrams and ERDs
│   └── clarifications/ ← client clarification requests
├── templates/       ← BR, CR, AI, BRD, PD, TIP, TC, DIA, ERD, MR, CLQ
├── preferences.json ← optional configuration
└── CLAUDE.md</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-950">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">three ways to add your code</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed"># Copy your project in
cp -r /path/to/your/project coderepo/

# Or symlink it (keeps one copy on disk)
ln -s /path/to/your/project coderepo/src

# Or clone a sub-repo into it
git clone https://github.com/your-org/your-project coderepo/</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-500">
        Anything you drop into <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> is gitignored and never committed — your code stays private to your machine.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-12">

      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">1</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Clone or copy the harness</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">git clone https://github.com/glovarix/agentic-ba.git
cd agentic-ba</pre>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Or copy the folder into an existing project repo. The harness is self-contained — it does not affect your project's code or CI.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">2</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Add your codebase</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Copy or symlink your project's source code into <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">coderepo/</code>. This is what Baxter reads to verify every artefact — required for everything except an initial BRD.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">cp -r /path/to/your/project coderepo/</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-800/40 dark:bg-amber-900/10">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300">Your code never leaves your machine</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">Everything inside <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> is gitignored — it is never committed or pushed. If your codebase is large, a symlink works just as well as a copy.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Baxter reads <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">coderepo/</code> to verify every artefact against your real codebase — checking technical feasibility, logic consistency, data model implications, role and permission logic, and flagging missing edge cases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">3</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Open in your AI agent</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Open the folder in your AI agent. Baxter's instructions are already in the right file for each tool — the agent loads them automatically with no setup.
        </p>

        <!-- Recommended for beginners -->
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border-2 border-primary-400 bg-primary-50 p-4 dark:border-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-950/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">Recommended for beginners</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">VS Code + the Claude Code extension</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
            If you are new to this, install <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 underline underline-offset-2 dark:text-primary-400">VS Code</a> and add the <strong>Claude Code extension</strong> from the marketplace. You get a familiar editor with Baxter running in a side panel — no terminal required. Open the <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">agentic-ba</code> folder, open the Claude Code panel, and start pasting requests.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          It works just as well in the Claude Code CLI, Cursor, or VS Code with GitHub Copilot — each picks up its own instruction file:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Tool</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Instruction file loaded automatically</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
              {[
                { tool: 'VS Code + Claude Code extension  (recommended)', file: 'CLAUDE.md' },
                { tool: 'Claude Code (CLI)', file: 'CLAUDE.md' },
                { tool: 'Cursor', file: '.cursor/rules/baxter.mdc' },
                { tool: 'GitHub Copilot', file: '.github/copilot-instructions.md' },
              ].map((row) => (
                <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">{row.tool}</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">{row.file}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          The instruction files are identical (both Claude Code editions read <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">CLAUDE.md</code>). A pre-commit hook keeps them in sync — edit <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">CLAUDE.md</code> and the others update automatically on your next commit. Run this once after cloning to activate it:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">git config core.hooksPath .githooks</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">4</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Paste a request — any raw text</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">example requests — paste exactly as received</div>
          <div class="space-y-3 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            <p>"The login page returns a 500 error when the user submits without a password"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"Write up the BRD for care plan cloning"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"I need test cases for the vitals module — mandatory fields and role access"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"Add a print to PDF button to the patient profile page"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Baxter classifies the request, tells you which template it will use, and asks for a one-word confirmation before generating anything. You can reply with the artefact code (e.g. <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">BR</code>), a number, or just <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">proceed</code>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Try it now callout -->
    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-indigo-200 bg-indigo-50 p-6 dark:border-indigo-800/40 dark:bg-indigo-900/10">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-400">Try every artefact — example prompts</p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Example prompts to get you started</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Add your codebase to <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code>, then paste any of the prompts below into Claude Code, Cursor, or GitHub Copilot. Baxter classifies the request, runs the full multi-dimensional sanity check against your source files, and asks before saving. These are illustrative — phrase yours however you like.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {[
          { icon: '📋', label: 'BRD', prompt: '"Write up the requirements for recurring invoices"' },
          { icon: '📖', label: 'PD', prompt: '"Document the authentication module"' },
          { icon: '🏗️', label: 'TIP', prompt: '"Write an implementation plan for the bulk import feature"' },
          { icon: '🧪', label: 'TC', prompt: '"Generate test cases for the billing module"' },
          { icon: '🐛', label: 'BR', prompt: '"The reports endpoint returns 500 when a duplicate name is submitted"' },
          { icon: '🔄', label: 'CR', prompt: '"Add a bulk export option to the orders list"' },
          { icon: '🤖', label: 'AI', prompt: '"We need an AI feature to auto-suggest categories from the item description"' },
          { icon: '📐', label: 'DIA', prompt: '"Diagram the checkout flow from API request to database"' },
          { icon: '🗂️', label: 'ERD', prompt: '"Draw an ERD for the orders and customers tables"' },
          { icon: '🗃️', label: "MR", prompt: '"/generate-module-registry — scan the codebase and build the module registry"' },
          { icon: '📋', label: "TP", prompt: '"/generate-test-plan artefacts/test-suites/Billing — synthesise a test plan and PDF"' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-indigo-200 bg-white p-3 dark:border-indigo-800/30 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-400">{item.icon} {item.label}</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs italic text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">{item.prompt}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter will classify each request, confirm the template, generate the artefact with a full sanity check, and ask before saving.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Artefact invocation reference -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What to say for each artefact</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter uses signal words to classify your request. You never need to name the template — just describe what you need. The table below shows the words Baxter listens for.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Artefact</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Signal words Baxter listens for</th>
              <th class="hidden px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white sm:table-cell">Template used</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { icon: '🐛', name: 'Bug Report (BR)', signals: '"not working", "broken", "error", "404", "500", "crash", "fails"', template: 'BR.md' },
              { icon: '🔄', name: 'Change Request (CR)', signals: '"add", "new", "improve", "enhance", "change", "feature request"', template: 'CR.md' },
              { icon: '🤖', name: 'AI Feature (AI)', signals: '"AI feature", "auto-fill", "auto-generate", "suggest", "LLM"', template: 'AI.md' },
              { icon: '📋', name: 'Business Requirements (BRD) — pre-dev', signals: '"BRD", "business requirements", "spec for", "write up the requirements"', template: 'BRD.md' },
              { icon: '📖', name: 'Product Documentation (PD) — post-dev', signals: '"PD", "document the module", "how it works", "what was built"', template: 'PD.md' },
              { icon: '🏗️', name: 'Implementation Plan (TIP)', signals: '"TIP", "implementation plan", "how to build", "dev plan"', template: 'TIP.md' },
              { icon: '🧪', name: 'Test Cases (TC)', signals: '"test cases", "test suite", "QA cases", "test steps"', template: 'TC.md' },
              { icon: '🗂️', name: 'Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)', signals: '"ERD", "entity relationship", "data model diagram", "draw the schema", "show the tables"', template: 'ERD.md' },
              { icon: '📐', name: 'Diagram (DIA)', signals: '"diagram", "flowchart", "mermaid", "draw", "visualise", "sequence diagram", "state diagram"', template: 'DIA.md' },
              { icon: '🗃️', name: 'Module Registry (MR) — power tool', signals: 'Run /generate-module-registry — Baxter scans the codebase and drafts the list for your review', template: '.claude/commands/generate-module-registry.md' },
              { icon: '📋', name: 'Test Plan (TP) — power tool', signals: 'Run /generate-test-plan [folder] — synthesises a 15-section test plan and PDF from the *_TC*.md files in the given folder', template: '.claude/commands/generate-test-plan.md' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span>{row.icon}</span>
                    <span class="font-medium text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">{row.name}</span>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.signals}</td>
                <td class="hidden px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 sm:table-cell">{row.template}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter applies the first match in priority order. If nothing matches, Baxter asks you one clarifying question.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Preferences -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Configuring Baxter</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Drop a <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">preferences.json</code> file in the project root to change how Baxter behaves. All settings are optional — Baxter runs on the defaults below if the file is absent.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">preferences.json — all defaults shown</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">{`{
  "commitArtefacts":       false,
  "pushAfterCommit":       false,
  "confirmBeforeSave":     true,
  "confirmBeforeCommit":   true,
  "confirmBeforeGenerate": true,
  "runSanityCheck":        true,
  "includeTechnicalNotes": true,
  "language":              "en-GB"
}`}</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Setting</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Default</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What it controls</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { key: 'commitArtefacts', default: 'false', description: 'Commit all artefacts to git. When false, only filenames starting with sample- are committed.' },
              { key: 'pushAfterCommit', default: 'false', description: 'Push to remote automatically after every commit. When false, you push manually.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeSave', default: 'true', description: 'Ask before writing any artefact file. Set to false to save immediately.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeCommit', default: 'true', description: 'Ask before running any git commit. Set to false to commit without prompting.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeGenerate', default: 'true', description: 'Announce the classified artefact type and ask for confirmation before generating. Set to false to skip straight to output.' },
              { key: 'runSanityCheck', default: 'true', description: 'Read coderepo/ and run the full sanity check after every applicable artefact. Set to false for faster, unverified drafts.' },
              { key: 'includeTechnicalNotes', default: 'true', description: 'Include the Technical Notes section in all artefacts. Set to false to omit it — useful for non-technical audiences.' },
              { key: 'language', default: '"en-GB"', description: 'Writing language. Use "en-GB" for UK English or "en-US" for US English.' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">{row.key}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500">{row.default}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.description}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- /compare-branches -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Comparing branches with <code class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">/compare-branches</code></h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter includes a built-in slash command for comparing two branch snapshots side by side. It produces Markdown files and converts them to PDFs — no HTML files left behind.
      </p>

      <!-- coderepo/branches callout -->
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-2 border-violet-400 bg-violet-50 p-5 dark:border-violet-700 dark:bg-violet-950/30">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">Where do branch snapshots go?</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">→ <code class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">coderepo/branches/</code></p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Each branch is a plain folder containing a copy of that branch's source code. The folder name becomes the branch label in the output.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-violet-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-violet-800">
          <pre class="p-4 text-xs text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">coderepo/
├── branches/
│   ├── <span class="text-violet-400 font-bold">my-app-production/</span>   ← production snapshot
│   └── <span class="text-violet-400 font-bold">my-app-staging/</span>      ← staging snapshot
└── (your main codebase here, if any)</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How to use it -->
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Output</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Audience</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Contents</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              {
                label: 'Technical',
                audience: 'Developers / tech leads',
                contents: 'New files, removed files, and a breakdown of every changed file grouped by functional area — with exact before/after behaviour per item.',
              },
              {
                label: 'Non-technical',
                audience: 'Product / QA / clinical leads',
                contents: 'Plain-English features and use cases: what users can do in each branch, colour-coded status badges, and a known-issues section.',
              },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400">{row.label}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.audience}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.contents}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">in Claude Code</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">/compare-branches
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Baxter asks: 1 Technical | 2 Non-technical | 3 Both</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Saves &#123;branch-a&#125;-vs-&#123;branch-b&#125;-diff.md + .pdf</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># and/or &#123;branch-a&#125;-vs-&#123;branch-b&#125;-usecases.md + .pdf</span></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        PDF generation uses <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">pandoc</code> if installed, or Chrome headless as a fallback. If there are more than two branch folders, Baxter lists them and asks which two to compare.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- /generate-module-registry -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Building a module registry with <code class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">/generate-module-registry</code></h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter uses <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">artefacts/modules/modules.md</code> to verify module names in every artefact. Run <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">/generate-module-registry</code> to generate it automatically from your codebase — no manual editing required.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Step</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What happens</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { step: '1. Scan', what: 'Baxter reads your codebase — routes, pages, navigation — and any existing artefacts.' },
              { step: '2. Draft', what: 'A module table is presented for your review. Edit any rows, add or remove modules.' },
              { step: '3. Save', what: 'Say "save" and Baxter writes artefacts/modules/modules.md. From that point, every artefact is verified against it.' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400 whitespace-nowrap">{row.step}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.what}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">in Claude Code</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">/generate-module-registry
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Baxter scans coderepo/ and drafts the module table</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Review, edit, then say "save"</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Writes → artefacts/modules/modules.md</span></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        The <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">context/</code> folder is free-form — drop in any project-specific reference files you need. Nothing in it is committed to git by default.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- /generate-test-plan -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Generating a test plan with <code class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">/generate-test-plan</code></h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Once you have a test suite folder full of <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">*_TC*.md</code> files, run <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">/generate-test-plan</code> to synthesise a complete, structured test plan — no manual drafting required. Baxter reads every test case, derives all sections from the actual content, and exports the result as both Markdown and PDF in a single step.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Step</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What happens</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { step: '1. Discover', what: 'Baxter reads every *_TC*.md file in the target folder, extracting ID, title, priority, type, source reference, and a precondition summary from each.' },
              { step: '2. Synthesise', what: 'Test areas are inferred from the TC sequence. Type counts, role requirements, data dependencies, ordering risks, and entry/exit criteria are all derived — nothing is invented.' },
              { step: '3. Save', what: 'Baxter writes [MODULE]_TEST_PLAN.md alongside the test cases. If a plan already exists, it offers to increment the version instead of overwriting.' },
              { step: '4. Export PDF', what: 'Immediately runs npx md-to-pdf on the saved file. The PDF is generated in the same folder — no separate step, no HTML files left behind.' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400 whitespace-nowrap">{row.step}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.what}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Section</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What it contains</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { section: 'Document Information', what: 'Version, date, status, prepared by, reviewed by' },
              { section: 'Introduction', what: 'Feature description and purpose of the plan, inferred from TC preconditions and area names' },
              { section: 'Test Objectives', what: 'One bullet per area stating what is being verified' },
              { section: 'Scope', what: 'In-scope checklist (one item per area) and explicit out-of-scope exclusions' },
              { section: 'Test Approach', what: 'Happy Path / Negative / Role-Based / Edge Case breakdown with counts and any ordering dependencies' },
              { section: 'Test Environments', what: 'Environment table and data prerequisites checklist derived from TC preconditions' },
              { section: 'User Roles Under Test', what: 'Roles, internal names, and areas covered — derived from TC preconditions' },
              { section: 'Area Coverage', what: 'Area name, TC range, count, and High priority TC IDs' },
              { section: 'TC Summary Table', what: 'All test cases: ID, title, area, type, priority — in one place' },
              { section: 'Entry / Exit Criteria', what: 'Concrete checklists — what must be true before testing starts and before sign-off' },
              { section: 'Dependencies and Risks', what: 'Risk table: data setup complexity, role-switching, ordering constraints, boundary data' },
              { section: 'Execution Schedule', what: 'Phased table with placeholder dates and owners for QA lead to complete' },
              { section: 'Defect Management', what: 'Required fields for every defect: TC ID, steps, expected/actual result, environment, severity P1–P4' },
              { section: 'Revision History', what: 'Version 1.0 with today\'s date — incremented automatically on subsequent runs' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300 whitespace-nowrap">{row.section}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.what}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">in Claude Code</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">/generate-test-plan artefacts/test-suites/SERVICES
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Baxter reads all SERVICES_TC*.md files</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Synthesises 15-section test plan, confirms filename</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Writes → SERVICES_TEST_PLAN.md</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500"># Exports → SERVICES_TEST_PLAN.pdf  (via npx md-to-pdf)</span></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Omit the folder path and Baxter lists the available test suites under <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">artefacts/test-suites/</code> for you to pick from.
      </p>
    </div>

